name: House Number 4 in the avenue. If you can't tell which one it is,  and say "I'm here to see Hazel" and if it's me, I'll tell you where the bathroom is. If I don't answer the door, then remember that there's a small basket full of stuffed toys in the hall
directions: Right at the top of the stairs. I'll tell you which one if you still don't know.
comment: Just straight up say you're trans and that a website said that this house has a gender neutral bathroom and that "your daughter said it was safe" . Also if a large, ogre like man answers the door, try not to talk to him. He's my dad and he's not very pleasant.

name: Bezirksamt Mitte - B√ºrgeramt Wedding

name: Ica Maxi

name: Charming charlie
comment: Walk in, ask for the bathroom and they'll say "through the exit sign then take a right"  they are labeled woman and men but no one watches you like a hawk which is great. There's no difference between the bathrooms, just use which everyone is open. Typically the men's bathroom is cleaner because it's rarely used. Super safe and clean. The employees won't care at all because they're probably  focused on a task.

In the big main building. Ground floor, the back corridor (not the one where the cafeteria is) that runs through the whole building. There are disabled gender neutral single stall bathrooms next to the womens and the mens bathrooms. The same in the basement next to the library.

name: Resale Carolina

comment: You don't have to be a paying customer but if you would at least look around a bit, that would mean the world to me; The thrift store is owned by my mom and her sister.  I'm actually there most days, if that makes you feel safer. (Also, the store isn't open Sundays and Mondays)

name: Brains Park

name: Archibald Park
directions: In carpark, entrance between 47 and 49 Beaubank road. Toilet block very visible on left.
comment: Public toilets. Often locked at night but not always. The accessible stall is most likely to be left unlocked.

name: Ethos Cafe and Bakery, East West Organics
directions: Back left corner of the cafe past the food counter and through another door (cafe is connected to the organics shop, but there aren't any toilets in that half).

name: Countrycide Church Unitarian Universalist

name: Barcade

name: Bahama Bucks
directions: In the back
It's all the way in the back by the kitchens.
